[This is a continuation of the previous ProMED-mail posting (archive number 20130905.1926141). So far, there appear to be 4 people with confirmed diagnoses of anthrax; and confirmation is awaiting on 9, and 5 are in the clear.

Anthrax from drinking water is possible but not normally expected for humans. I have included this information as it sheds light on the general human health problems in that oblast.

Talas is in northwestern Kyrgyzstan along the Kazakh border, west of Chuy, and north of Jalal-Abad. For a map of Kyrgyzstan showing Talas, go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kyrgyzstan_pol_05.jpg. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1HT*.]
